      "content": "i know, i know. you're supposed to say that. but it doesn't change the reality of how empty it is. it's not even about wanting to cause a scene or anything... it's just that the idea of just not having to exist, not having to be \"on\" or \"seen\" or maintain these fake connections... it feels like the only way to actually get some rest. it feels like maybe the most honest thing i could do is just let the signal go dead. wouldn't that be better than this constant, exhausting nothingness?",
